# Coding Standards

This project uses the uncompromising-standards hook. See: https://github.com/uncompromising-standards

## Key Rules

- No unwrap/expect/panic - use proper error handling
- No bare arithmetic (+ - * / %) - use .saturating_* methods
- No direct array indexing - use .get() instead
- No dynamic allocation (vec!, Box, HashMap, Arc, Rc)
- No unsafe code
- Single-letter vars only: i, j, k, x, y, z
- Max function length: 50 lines
- Max file length: 200 lines

## Fixing Errors

When the hook blocks a write, the error message will tell you:
- What pattern is forbidden
- What line it's on
- How to fix it (e.g., use .get() instead of [i])
